  "firstAcquaintance": "A devout follower of the Holy Mother Church, quite reserved in manner, wielding a one-handed sword as her weapon. Even when captured by the demon race and enslaved, her faith in the Holy Mother Church never wavered.",
  "personality": "Honest, conservative, and earnest, she is a deeply devout follower of the Holy Mother Church, tirelessly conveying the teachings time and time again.",
  "like": "Winged statues, Noelle's personal belongings",
  "familiarData": "Her mother was a devout believer of the kingdom's religion. Born on the wastelands, Falei was instilled from childhood with the belief that Noelle would one day save all of humanity.\nWhen their hideout was discovered by slave traders, she and Noelle were captured while trying to escape, and both were reduced to slavery. Honest and devout by nature, having never personally experienced tragic hardship, she never imagined how evil people's hearts could become.\nHer knowledge, understanding of intimacy, and habits are all very traditional and conservative. Because she took care of Noelle from a young age, she has excellent domestic skills and is adept at looking after others. She desperately wishes to obtain one of Noelle's personal items, believing it would bring her blessings, but church doctrine forbids taking them without permission. But if someone were to obtain one for her through other means...",
